y, I can still check for the same semantics and maintain some level of coverage, even if it doesn’t cover the bridge class directly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating log4j API usage**\\n\\nI’m looking into whether the ParameterizedMessage constructors in log4j-api are deprecated, especially for version 3.0.0-alpha1. I might need to check the log4j-api sources, but I need to focus strictly on open-source files related to the error output. It seems that I could consider using MessageFactory2 instead, as ParameterizedMessageFactory may still be valid. Log4j 2 shows that ParameterizedMessage constructors detect exceptions in their arguments, which is important for handling errors.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing ParameterizedMessage usage**\\n\\nI'm examining how LocationAwareLog uses the new ParameterizedMessage constructor. It appears to rely on the throwable being detected correctly, especially if it's null. I’m considering renaming a test to reflect how Log4jLogger behaves. The old test had simpler messages, but I might need to use SimpleMessage or ObjectMessage for better coverage. I’m also pondering whether I should check the source for version 2.24.3 to find replaced classes. It could be useful to search through the repository for any references to ThrowableConsuming to clarify this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rmwvmXUDtWPiH3jCs0mrVCRK|fc_085f145bcf7f6d4c016a0d731a5e5c81958de2dcd8f90b3876", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"ThrowableConsumingMessageFactory|throwableConsumingMessageFactory\" -n . /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1383, "output": 972, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21299, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestam