[thinking] **Considering test dependencies**
[thinking] 
[thinking] For our test, I’m thinking about adding a core dependency and capturing it, but that could broaden the scope. It seems necessary to maintain semantics. The current test uses LogManager's root runtime without requiring the core compile. To include the core would mean adding more, which could be intrusive, even though it should remain minimal. I wonder if using log4j-slf4j2-impl version 2.24.3 would be a good solution.
[thinking] 
